body:
/kind bug

**Description**
I am currently evaluating podman + nftables with the CNI nftables plugin from [greenpau](https://github.com/greenpau/cni-plugins) but I am already stuck with simple setup (rootfull httpd container with port forwarding). Right now I am not sure if this is a bug in podman, a misunderstanding on my site or a missing nftable rule.\
After setting up the network and container I cannot connect **from localhost** to the httpd server. The 'external' connection works fine so far.


**Steps to reproduce the issue:**

1. Install the CNI plugins as described here: [https://github.com/greenpau/cni-plugins](https://github.com/greenpau/cni-plugins)
2. Setup the network with the following config file in `/etc/cni/net.d/87-podman-bridge.conflist `:
```
{
  "cniVersion": "0.4.0",
  "name": "podman",
  "plugins": [
    {
      "type": "bridge",
      "bridge": "cni-podman0",
      "isGateway": true,
      "ipMasq": false,
      "ipam": {
        "type": "host-local",
        "routes": [{ "dst": "0.0.0.0/0" }],
        "ranges": [
          [
            {
              "subnet": "10.88.0.0/16",
              "gateway": "10.88.0.1"
            }
          ]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "cni-nftables-portmap",
      "capabilities": {
        "portMappings": true
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "cni-nftables-firewall",
      "forward_chain_name": "forward"
    }
  ]
}
```
3. Setup a container as described on podman.io:
`sudo podman run -dt -p 80:8080/tcp registry.fedoraproject.org/f29/httpd`

**Describe the results you received:**

**Output of `podman network ls`:**
```
NAME    VERSION  PLUGINS
podman  0.4.0    bridge,cni-nftables-portmap,cni-nftables-firewall
```

Before setting up the container I flushed all nftable rules and let the CNI plugin do its thing.

**Output of `nft list ruleset`:**
